        <p>Anxiety is one of the most common mental health conditions, affecting millions worldwide. It often presents as excessive worry, racing thoughts, restlessness, irritability, fatigue, and sleep disturbances. These symptoms can significantly disrupt daily life and relationships. Identifying triggers early can prevent escalation. Coping strategies such as deep breathing, meditation, regular physical activity, and structured routines can make a big difference. Therapy, especially Cognitive Behavioral Therapy (CBT), is highly effective. Journaling, spending time in nature, and limiting caffeine or alcohol also help. Building a support system and practicing self-compassion are key steps toward healing. This article explores practical, proven methods to manage anxiety holistically.</p>
